<div id="review_44315799" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/44315799" />
    <a title="Jessica Haider" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/102314-jessica-haider"><img alt="Jessica Haider" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1599225626p2/102314.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/44315799?book_show_action=true">Jul 11, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jessica Haider" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jessica Haider" href="/user/show/102314-jessica-haider">Jessica Haider</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780143114130" href="/book/show/2629425-the-sharper-your-knife-the-less-you-cry">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/102314-jessica-haider?shelf=food">food</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/102314-jessica-haider?shelf=memoir">memoir</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/102314-jessica-haider?shelf=follow-your-bliss">follow-your-bliss</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer44315799" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1572439981273717721">Kathleen Flinn was 35 when she got laid off from her job writing web content. As an American working in London she is far from family and friends. She decides to take this as an opportunity to pursue her dream of going to Le Cordon Bleu culinary school in Paris. Her boyfriend moves from Seattle to live in Paris with her while she attends school. We hear of her lessons at school, including her failures and her successes. Each chapter includes a recipe at the end that relates to that chapter. <br/> The</span>
  <span id="freeText1572439981273717721" style="display:none">Kathleen Flinn was 35 when she got laid off from her job writing web content. As an American working in London she is far from family and friends. She decides to take this as an opportunity to pursue her dream of going to Le Cordon Bleu culinary school in Paris. Her boyfriend moves from Seattle to live in Paris with her while she attends school. We hear of her lessons at school, including her failures and her successes. Each chapter includes a recipe at the end that relates to that chapter. <br /> The writers voice and humor shines throughout this book. It definitely tempted me to go to culinary school.<br /><br /><b>What to Listen to While Reading (or during reading breaks)</b><br />(Just Like) Starting Over by John Lennon<br />Changes by Langhorne Slim<br />Paradis Perdus by Christine and the Queens<br />La Vie en Rose by Louis Armstrong<br />Feeling Good by Nina Simone<br /></span>
