<div id="review_655445287" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/655445287" />
    <a title="Kathye Allen" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/17161359-kathye-allen"><img alt="Kathye Allen" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1360072795p2/17161359.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/655445287?book_show_action=true">Jun 30, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kathye Allen" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kathye Allen" href="/user/show/17161359-kathye-allen">Kathye Allen</a>
      </span>

          added it



          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">anyone who likes to read and cook</span></div>

          <div>
    <span class="greyText">Recommended to Kathye by: </span>
      Cathy Glinski
  </div>


    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer655445287" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5430953413634502294">While I have never had the urge to live in Paris or attend Le Courdon Bleu, I throughly enjoyed the authors telling of her time there. If you like to cook or travel or both, you will find this a good easy read. For anyone (myself included)who likes to read cookbooks like novels the fact that Ms Flinn includes some very tasyt sound receipes is just the icing on the cake.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


